        "rendered": "Audio Block"
    },
    "content": {
        "rendered": "\n<p class=\"has-text-align-right has-small-font-size\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/blocks/\">Go back to the list of <strong>Blocks</strong></a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Creating an&nbsp;<em>audio block</em>&nbsp;will allow you to embed a piece of music, podcast, or other sound file right into your page or post.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In order to add an&nbsp;<em>audio block</em>, click on the inserter icon. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-video\"><video controls src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/Audio-block-WP-62.mp4\"></video></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also type /audio and hit enter in a new paragraph block to add one quickly.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/audio-block-select-WP-62-2.png\" alt=\"When you type /audio the editor suggest adding an audio block, a SoundCloud, Spotify, Mixcloud or Pocket Casts embed.\" class=\"wp-image-16356329\" style=\"width:328px;height:277px\" width=\"328\" height=\"277\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/audio-block-select-WP-62-2.png 328w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/audio-block-select-WP-62-2-300x253.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 328px) 100vw, 328px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Use the slash command /audio to insert an&nbsp;<em>audio block.</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/adding-a-new-block/\">Detailed instructions on adding blocks</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"block-interface\">Block Interface</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Every block comes with unique toolbar icons and block-specific user controls that allow you to manipulate the block right in the editor.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1508963/156562575-6535b885-250e-4148-9369-2d923b448b40.png\" alt=\"The audio block toolbar.\" style=\"width:358px;height:96px\" width=\"358\" height=\"96\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">The&nbsp;<em>audio block</em>&nbsp;has an alignment toolbar icon.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"adding-files\">Adding Files</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>When you add an&nbsp;<em>audio block</em>, you get three options:&nbsp;<em>Upload, Media Library,</em>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em>Insert from URL.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1508963/156562576-77cb4e11-89ec-4fab-ad09-1659d0ddaca3.png\" alt=\"The\u00a0audio block\u00a0allows you to Upload Media, use media in your Library, or add from a custom URL.\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">The&nbsp;<em>audio block</em>&nbsp;allows you to Upload Media, use media in your Library, or add from a custom URL.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Upload will allow you to upload a new audio file from your computer. Media Library lets you select a file that\u2019s already uploaded to your site\u2019s Media Library. Insert from URL lets you input a URL where the file has already been uploaded, on WordPress.com or elsewhere on the web.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you\u2019ve selected your audio file you can start configuring your&nbsp;<em>audio block</em>!</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"alignment\">Alignment</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>When you select your<em>&nbsp;audio block</em>, a toolbar will appear where you can change block&#8217;s alignment. Choosing right or left will allow you to place another block alongside the&nbsp;<em>audio block</em>. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-28f84493 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66%\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"506\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-alignment-WP-62-1024x506.png\" alt=\"Alignment settings for the audio block.\" class=\"wp-image-16356335\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-alignment-WP-62-1024x506.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-alignment-WP-62-300x148.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-alignment-WP-62-768x379.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-alignment-WP-62.png 1336w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:50%\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>None&nbsp;</strong>\u2013 Default alignment option.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Wide width&nbsp;</strong>\u2013 Increase the width of the post beyond the content size.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Full width</strong>&nbsp;\u2013 Extend the block to cover the full width of the screen.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Align left</strong>&nbsp;\u2013 Make the block left-aligned.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Align center&nbsp;</strong>\u2013 Make the block alignment centered.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Align right&nbsp;</strong>\u2013 Make the block right aligned.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"edit-audio\">Replace Audio</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This is another option in the&nbsp;<em>audio block\u2019s</em>&nbsp;toolbar. Choosing this will allow you to select a new audio file for your block. Use this if you need to replace the audio file in your&nbsp;<em>audio block</em>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-replace-WP-62-1024x428.png\" alt=\"When you select the Replace option in the block toolbar you can choose between opening the media library or uploading a file.\nThere is also information about the URL to the current media file.\" class=\"wp-image-16356336\" style=\"width:512px;height:214px\" width=\"512\" height=\"214\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-replace-WP-62-1024x428.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-replace-WP-62-300x125.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-replace-WP-62-768x321.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-replace-WP-62.png 1336w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Caption</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If your audio file has a caption in the Media Library, it is shown below the audio player:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/Audio-block-caption-1-WP-62-1024x265.png\" alt=\"The caption is below the audio player.\" class=\"wp-image-16356331\" style=\"width:512px;height:133px\" width=\"512\" height=\"133\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/Audio-block-caption-1-WP-62-1024x265.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/Audio-block-caption-1-WP-62-300x78.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/Audio-block-caption-1-WP-62-768x199.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/Audio-block-caption-1-WP-62.png 1336w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If your file does not have a caption in the Media library, you can add a custom caption by selecting the Add caption option in the toolbar:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-add-caption-WP-62-1024x208.png\" alt=\"The Add caption option is in the block toolbar next to the alignment options.\" class=\"wp-image-16356332\" style=\"width:512px;height:104px\" width=\"512\" height=\"104\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-add-caption-WP-62-1024x208.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-add-caption-WP-62-300x61.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-add-caption-WP-62-768x156.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-add-caption-WP-62.png 1336w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Both the Media Library caption and the placeholder text are editable. Select the caption to edit the text. You can use the caption toolbar to make the text bold or italic, or add a link. Select the arrow icon in the toolbar to access more options:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-caption-toolbar-WP-62-1024x661.png\" alt=\"The caption has a toolbar with options for making selected text bold or italic, an option to add a link, and a &quot;more options&quot; menu.\nMore options include highlighting text, inline code, inline image, and more.\" class=\"wp-image-16356333\" style=\"width:512px;height:331px\" width=\"512\" height=\"331\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-caption-toolbar-WP-62-1024x661.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-caption-toolbar-WP-62-300x194.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-caption-toolbar-WP-62-768x496.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-caption-toolbar-WP-62.png 1336w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can remove a caption by selecting the Remove caption button in the toolbar:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-remove-caption-WP-62-1024x281.png\" alt=\"The Remove caption option is in the block toolbar next to the alignment options.\" class=\"wp-image-16356334\" style=\"width:512px;height:141px\" width=\"512\" height=\"141\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-remove-caption-WP-62-1024x281.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-remove-caption-WP-62-300x82.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-remove-caption-WP-62-768x210.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-remove-caption-WP-62.png 1336w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">More Options </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>These controls give you the option to copy, duplicate, and edit your block as HTML.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/more-options/\">Read about these and other settings.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"sidebar-settings\">Block Settings</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Every block has specific options in the editor sidebar in addition to the options found in the block toolbar.&nbsp;<em>If you do not see the sidebar, simply click the \u2018settings\u2019 icon next to the Publish button.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/WP-62-block-editor-settings-icon.png\" alt=\"The settings sidebar can be opened using the Settings the button next to the Publish button.\" class=\"wp-image-16356337\" style=\"width:325px;height:120px\" width=\"325\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/WP-62-block-editor-settings-icon.png 650w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/WP-62-block-editor-settings-icon-300x111.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 325px) 100vw, 325px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">The block settings can be found in the sidebar.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Settings tab</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-settings-tab-WP-62.png\" alt=\"The audio settings for the audio block are in the block settings sidebar.\" class=\"wp-image-16356495\" style=\"width:464px;height:710px\" width=\"464\" height=\"710\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-settings-tab-WP-62.png 618w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-settings-tab-WP-62-196x300.png 196w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 464px) 100vw, 464px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"autoplay-loop\">Autoplay &amp; Loop</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>These options let you set your audio file to autoplay when someone visits the page or post. Looping lets you choose if the audio file repeats after it\u2019s finished.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"preload\">Preload</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>This option allows you to select how much of the audio file is downloaded when the page or post is loaded. While it may be tempting to go ahead and have the whole file download automatically, keep in mind that this can slow your page\u2019s load speed down.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are four settings:</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Browser default</strong>&nbsp;\u2013 Use settings from site visitor&#8217;s browser.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Auto</strong>&nbsp;\u2013 The entire audio file is downloaded, regardless of whether the visitor clicks the Play button or not. This makes the biggest impact on your page or post\u2019s load speed, especially with larger audio files.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Metadata</strong>&nbsp;\u2013 Only basic info about the file will be downloaded automatically. Like the None option, the download of the audio file only begins when someone clicks Play. This setting is also very fast, as the only thing downloaded is text. On a fundamental level, there\u2019s not a big difference between None and Metadata.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>None</strong>&nbsp;\u2013 Nothing about the audio file is downloaded automatically. The download of the audio file only begins when your visitor clicks the Play button. This is the fastest setting.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Advanced</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>The advanced tab lets you add a CSS class to your block, allowing you to write custom CSS and style the block as you see fit.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1508963/157893362-4a01d92a-df33-44fd-a68b-4bcf505c497b.png\" alt=\"The advanced tab for the audio block.\" style=\"width:337px;height:392px\" width=\"337\" height=\"392\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">The advanced section lets you add an HTML anchor and a CSS class to your block.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Styles tab</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-styles-tab-WP-62.png\" alt=\"The style settings for the audio block are in the Styles tab in the block settings sidebar.\" class=\"wp-image-16356496\" style=\"width:309px;height:473px\" width=\"309\" height=\"473\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-styles-tab-WP-62.png 618w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-styles-tab-WP-62-196x300.png 196w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 309px) 100vw, 309px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Dimensions</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Audio&nbsp;block </strong>provides dimension settings options to add padding and margin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For details refer to this support article: <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/dimension-controls-overview/\">Dimension settings overview</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Troubleshooting</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you try to upload a file type that is not supported, the editor will display a notice with an error message:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-unsupported-format-WP-62.png\" alt=\"The error message includes the file name followed by the text &quot;Sorry this file type is not supported here.&quot;\" class=\"wp-image-16356338\" style=\"width:458px;height:70px\" width=\"458\" height=\"70\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-unsupported-format-WP-62.png 916w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-unsupported-format-WP-62-300x46.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/04/audio-block-unsupported-format-WP-62-768x117.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 458px) 100vw, 458px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group changelog has-very-dark-gray-color has-very-light-gray-background-color has-text-color has-background is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\" id=\"changelog\">Changelog </h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated 2023-03-29\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated information about the caption option</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated images</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2022-11-25\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Added Alt text to a few images </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Replaces redundant content </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2022-03-15\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Update screenshots for 5.9</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Update alignment and replace sections content</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Add More options section</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2022-03-03\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Update screenshots for 5.9</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2020-06-18\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Added &#8216;Link back to blocks&#8217; to the top of the page</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Replace the &#8216;Advanced&#8217; section with the &#8216;Advanced settings&#8217; reusable block</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Created 2019-03-07</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n",
